4:
The magic and the music were
awesome! I want to be a mage
when I grow up, too!
7:
It was certainly a wild ride, but
Magia Fest is finally over...
11:
Sure is... For a moment I really had
no idea what was going to happen,
but I'm glad everything turned out
all right.
15:
We were lucky that so little damage
to structures was done.
17:
We had almost no injuries thanks to
your help, so I'm relieved as well.
20:
...Although as a student of the
academy, I'm feeling somewhat
apprehensive about all the cleanup
and repairs waiting for me
tomorrow...
23:
Right, yeah... I imagine there will be a
lot that needs doing.
26:
Ah, Luciada! There you are. You got
a second?
29: Oh, hello Sarah. I've... got a second?
32:
You're not in trouble with anything,
are you?
35:
No, not at all! You've been super
busy with work lately, right? It's a
shame, because our club opened a
shop recently...
36:
And you still haven't stopped by!
Everyone's waiting for you, so why
don't you just drop in for a little bit?
39: All right, then. Let's have a little look!
42:
Oh, something going on over there?
You can go ahead and take our
leftover cake with you.
44:
Oh, President! After you're done,
would you mind stopping by and
seeing our club's display, too?
47:
Hey, Luciada. Are you part of a club
yourself?
50:
I am part of the Golem Club, as a
matter of fact!
55:
...Wait, THAT Golem Club?! You're
talking about those things always
going on a rampage on campus?
61:
What the heck is a golem-touching
maid cafe?
64:
As its name implies, it's a maid cafe
that allows its guests to interact with
golems up close. This cafe was my
idea, as well!
68: Do you really need maids here?
72:
Of course we do! Just look at
Stella—she's having a wonderful
time competing with a maid in
golem wrestling.
77:
What does golem wrestling have to
do with maids, though?
79:
That golem was so awesome.
Amicitia... right? That was incredible!
82:
I never expected the transformation,
myself!
84:
Maybe our club should work on
implementing transformation
mechanisms into our own golems.
Or maybe a fusion function should
come first?
87:
There you guys are! Why're you off
having fun without me?
91:
Hehe, sorry Nao. Would you accept
our apology if we gave you cake?
100:
Congrats! You've won a group
discount coupon to a cake buffet!
107:
Oh, good work, Stella! That's a very
nice dessert cafe!
112:
Yes. I look forward to going there
together.
126:
But... are you sure? Wouldn't you
rather bring a friend along instead
of me?
131:
You hear that, Stella? Luciada thinks
we're not friends!
146:
When cleanup's all finished around
here, we'd love if you came to
Starview Village.
155:
...Of course, I'd love to go! I look
forward to continuing to work
together!
160:
Hey! How late are you all planning
on sticking around for?! Hurry up
and get ready to go home!
174:
What's wrong, Luciada? Did you
forget something?
181:
It's just...
It's really all over now, huh?
192:
Perhaps once things calm down a
little more, I'll be able to honestly say
I enjoyed myself. But I feel like I'm still
processing everything...
195:
I don't know if it would be okay to
say "I had fun" after such an
experience...
201:
At the very least, I can say with
confidence that I did everything I
could.
213:
Hey, what's taking you guys so long!
I already made the reservations so
let's get a move-on!
219:
Hehe. It feels like we're all
classmates or something.
